<item>
            <title>[SEC-3169] Security context is propagated but not cloned in @Async methods</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-3169</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In Wildfly with Java EE, whenever you run an asynchronous task using @Asynchronous, the security context is getting cloned and then pushed to the new async thread.&lt;br/&gt;
see bug:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-2016&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-2016&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
and commit:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/wildfly/wildfly/pull/5013/files&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/wildfly/wildfly/pull/5013/files&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In Spring Security though, the strategy to propagate the security context is a bit different. Instead of cloning the context, the reference to the context is propagated to the new async thread.&lt;/p&gt;

