&lt;p/&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can lead to concurrency issue if the new async thread alter the security context.&lt;br/&gt;
Ex:&lt;br/&gt;
1. an authenticated user trigger something asynchronous and the processing of its request is not over&lt;br/&gt;
2. within the asynchronous thread we eventually push another principal to let say execute a job on behalf of a system user&lt;br/&gt;
3. meanwhile the processing of the original request continue but now with the new system user principal which can lead to weird behavior&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could it be possible to re-implement the Security Context to be duplicated instead to avoid the issue?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alternatively, instead of duplicating everything, we could at least duplicate the authentication information which is immutable:&lt;/p&gt;
